Algorithm: Banking System Simulation

Step 1: Start

Step 2: Initialize variables

Declare account number, name, balance
Set initial balance (e.g., 0 or minimum balance)

Step 3: Display Menu

Show options:
Create Account
Deposit Money
Withdraw Money
Check Balance
Exit

Step 4: Accept user choice

Step 5: Use decision structure (switch or if-else)

Case 1: Create Account
Input account number and customer name
Set initial balance
Display “Account Created Successfully”

Case 2: Deposit Money
Input deposit amount
Add amount to balance
Display updated balance

Case 3: Withdraw Money
Input withdrawal amount
Check if balance ≥ withdrawal amount
If yes → subtract amount from balance
If no → display “Insufficient Balance”

Case 4: Check Balance
Display current balance

Case 5: Exit
Terminate the program

Step 6: Repeat menu until user selects Exit

Step 7: Stop
